  ./COVERAGE.md:387:| `io.circe:circe-core_3` | [0.14.10<br>- 0.15.0-M1](metadata/io.circe/circe-core_3/index.json) | <details><summary>Show</summary> Circe Core provides the core JSON data model and type classes for encoding and decoding JSON in Scala. It includes the JSON AST, cursor APIs, codec abstractions, printers, parser interfaces, and standard instances used by other Circe modules.</details> | [100.0% (0/0 calls)](stats/io.circe/circe-core_3/) |
  ./COVERAGE.md:388:| `io.circe:circe-generic_3` | [0.14.12<br>- 0.14.15](metadata/io.circe/circe-generic_3/index.json) | <details><summary>Show</summary> circe-generic provides automatic and semi-automatic derivation of Circe Encoder and Decoder instances for Scala case classes and sealed traits. It lets Scala 3 applications convert domain types to and from JSON through Circe's type class APIs with minimal boilerplate.</details> | [100.0% (0/0 calls)](stats/io.circe/circe-generic_3/) |
  ./COVERAGE.md:389:| `io.circe:circe-jawn_3` | [0.14.12<br>- 0.14.15](metadata/io.circe/circe-jawn_3/index.json) | <details><summary>Show</summary> Circe Jawn integrates the Circe JSON data model with the Jawn JSON parser for Scala. It provides parser and facade implementations that read JSON text into Circe Json values and support Circe's higher-level parsing modules.</details> | [100.0% (0/0 calls)](stats/io.circe/circe-jawn_3/) |
  ./COVERAGE.md:390:| `io.circe:circe-numbers_3` | [0.14.10<br>- 0.15.0-M1](metadata/io.circe/circe-numbers_3/index.json) | <details><summary>Show</summary> Circe Numbers provides numeric value support for Circe's JSON model, centered on the BiggerDecimal representation used for JSON numbers. It supplies Scala 3 JVM classes for preserving numeric precision and converting between decimal and integral forms in Circe.</details> | [100.0% (0/0 calls)](stats/io.circe/circe-numbers_3/) |
  ./COVERAGE.md:391:| `io.circe:circe-parser_3` | [0.14.12<br>- 0.14.15](metadata/io.circe/circe-parser_3/index.json) | <details><summary>Show</summary> Circe Parser provides JSON parsing functions for the Circe Scala JSON library. It exposes parser APIs that turn JSON text into Circe Json values using the Jawn-based parsing implementation.</details> | [100.0% (0/0 calls)](stats/io.circe/circe-parser_3/) |
